@SleepygiantXL Color illusion is true.  The JPEG file format is lossy meaning you lose image information, including color, when the image is saved.  In this case some of the color information was lost and the inner rings ended up being off the original shade by a hair because of the compression.  However, they are still the same color.

@Username636 They are the same color.  Go into GIMP, use the color selection tool, select the green or blue ring and you will select both rings.  If you then flip the center rings you will notice that the image does not change: the left is still green and the right is still blue.  You can even copy one ring over the other and you will not change what you see because they are the same color.
